=== RAW MODEL ANSWER ===
Answer: Step 1: From trans-4-aminocyclopentane-1-carboxylic acid, make the protected chiral branch tert-butyl (1R,4S)-4-aminocyclopentane-1-carboxylate (esterify the acid; keep/protect the amine as needed). | Step 2: Build the heterobiaryl boronate by SNAr of 2,4-dibromopyridine (or similar bromopyridine) with 4-fluorobenzylamine to give 4-bromo-2-(4-fluorobenzylamino)pyridine, then Miyaura borylation to 4-(4-fluorobenzylamino)pyridin-3-yl-Bpin. | Step 3: Suzuki-couple this boronate onto 2,4,5-trichloropyridine at C4 to give 2,5-dichloro-4-(4-(4-fluorobenzylamino)pyridin-3-yl)pyridine. | Step 4: Buchwald–Hartwig amination of the remaining C2 chloride with tert-butyl (1R,4S)-4-aminocyclopentane-1-carboxylate to furnish the coupled protected intermediate. | Step 5: Global deprotection/hydrolysis (TFA to remove tert-butyl/Boc groups, then workup/LiOH as needed) to deliver O=C(O)[C@H]1CC[C@@H](Nc2cc(-c3cccc(NCc4cccc(F)c4)n3)c(Cl)cn2)C1.

=== NORMALIZED STUDENT ANSWER ===
Step 1: From trans-4-aminocyclopentane-1-carboxylic acid, make the protected chiral branch tert-butyl (1R,4S)-4-aminocyclopentane-1-carboxylate (esterify the acid; keep/protect the amine as needed). | Step 2: Build the heterobiaryl boronate by SNAr of 2,4-dibromopyridine (or similar bromopyridine) with 4-fluorobenzylamine to give 4-bromo-2-(4-fluorobenzylamino)pyridine, then Miyaura borylation to 4-(4-fluorobenzylamino)pyridin-3-yl-Bpin. | Step 3: Suzuki-couple this boronate onto 2,4,5-trichloropyridine at C4 to give 2,5-dichloro-4-(4-(4-fluorobenzylamino)pyridin-3-yl)pyridine. | Step 4: Buchwald–Hartwig amination of the remaining C2 chloride with tert-butyl (1R,4S)-4-aminocyclopentane-1-carboxylate to furnish the coupled protected intermediate. | Step 5: Global deprotection/hydrolysis (TFA to remove tert-butyl/Boc groups, then workup/LiOH as needed) to deliver O=C(O)[C@H]1CC[C@@H](Nc2cc(-c3cccc(NCc4cccc(F)c4)n3)c(Cl)cn2)C1.

